    <refpurpose>Add new ligature to font</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <para>#include &lt;pslib.h&gt;</para>
		<para>void &funcname;(PSDoc *psdoc, int fontid, const char *glyphname1, const char *glyphname2, const char *glyphname3)</para>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>Adds a new ligature to an already loaded font. This function
		  was mainly provided to add ligatures to Type3 fonts created
			with <function>PS_begin_font(3)</function>, but it can also be used
			for fonts loaded with <function>PS_findfont(3)</function>.</para>
		<para><function>&funcname;</function> has been introduced in version
		  0.4.0 of pslib.</para>

  </refsect1>
